Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.24,0:21:35.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,知道吗 我们可以看到我们自己星系的部分旋臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You know, we can see parts of spiral arms in our own galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.04,0:21:37.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们估摸它们整个联系在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we figure that they're all connected...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.04,0:21:41.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有点像我们可以从外面看到的其它星系的旋臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}kind of like the spiral arms of other galaxies...that we can see from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.50,0:21:45.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们知道银河系的四条主要的旋臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know that the Milky Way's four main spiral arms...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.01,0:21:50.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从闹市区像大街那样展开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}swing out from the downtown center like wide streets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.47,0:21:55.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从里到外给它们分别取名:矩尺座旋臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From the inside out, they're named Norma...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.35,0:21:56.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,南十字座旋臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scutum-Crux...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.27,0:21:58.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,人马座旋臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sagittarius...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.52,0:22:00.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,英仙座旋臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and Perseus.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.07,0:22:06.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,假如旋臂是星系的郊区的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lfthe arms are the galaxy's suburbs...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.70,0:22:10.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么我们的太阳系就居住在安静的大街尽头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then our solar system lives on a quiet, dead-end street...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.28,0:22:15.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在人马座旋臂和英仙座旋臂之间的所谓猎户座支臂上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between Sagittarius and Perseus on what's called the Orion Spur.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.87,0:22:18.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,银河系里所有的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All the stars in the Milky Way...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.54,0:22:22.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,组成了一个约2000到4000亿的社会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}add up to a community of about 200 to 400 billion...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.84,0:22:25.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们都在移动之中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they're on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.21,0:22:26.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们围绕着星系运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We are orbiting around the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.84,0:22:28.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们改变了我们的位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We change our position.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.22,0:22:30.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,迄今为止 我们认为太阳总是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So far, we think the Sun has always been...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.05,0:22:32.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,与中心保持着同样的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about the same distance away from the center...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.18,0:22:33.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是我们已经进出了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we've been in and out...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.22,0:22:35.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里几乎所有的旋臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of pretty much every spiral arm that there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.73,0:22:40.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,螺旋形被称为密度波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spirals are called density waves...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.69,0:22:43.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里的恒星和气体被推挤在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}areas where the stars and gas get pushed together.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.94,0:22:47.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,由于密度波的盘旋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the density waves spiral around...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.44,0:22:50.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,数十亿颗恒星穿行其中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the billions of stars ride over and through them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.49,0:22:54.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦你想起环法自行车赛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you think about watching the Tour de France...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.41,0:22:55.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你就可以看到所有的那些自行车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you see all of these bicycles.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.91,0:22:57.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们都在向前行进\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're all moving forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.25,0:23:00.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有时他们会簇拥在一条车道上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sometimes they kind of clump up around one bicyclist.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.21,0:23:01.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有时他们会绵延而行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And sometimes they're stretched out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.96,0:23:03.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那有点像旋臂的模样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's sort of what the spiral arms are like...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.75,0:23:06.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星就像赛车那样转动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the stars are going around like the bicyclists...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.42,0:23:07.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有时在成堆簇拥的地区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sometimes in clumpy areas...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.88,0:23:10.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有时在绵延伸展的区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and sometimes in more spread-out areas...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.09,0:23:12.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是它们都围绕着中心运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but they keep going around the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.55,0:23:17.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星通常不单独行动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars don't usually travel alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.81,0:23:22.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,与此同时 球状星团居住在星系的光环里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While giant globular clusters populate the galaxy's halo...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.10,0:23:26.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,银河盘已经散开 即银河星团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the galactic disk has open or galactic clusters.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.27,0:23:27.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些成堆的年轻恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These bundles of young stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.98,0:23:31.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就靠它们之间的引力结合在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are barely held together by their mutual gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.28,0:23:36.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在 "疏散星团"意味着恒星实际上可以自由来去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, "open cluster" implies that the stars are actually free to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.45,0:23:37.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它是开放的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt is open.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.54,0:23:38.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此通常这个星团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So this is a cluster, usually...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.91,0:23:41.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是由许多恒星结合在一起形成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of many stars that have formed together...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.12,0:23:44.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都是来自这些巨大的尘埃和气体云其中的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all from one of these giant clouds of dust and gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.17,0:23:46.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着时间的推移它们将相互远离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over time, they're going to move away from each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.88,0:23:48.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,分别散布在星系四处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}distribute themselves around the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.59,0:23:55.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家已经计算出了银河系里约有两万个疏散星团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers have counted about 20,000 open clusters in the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.05,0:23:59.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,昴宿星团是已知最接近地球的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Pleiades is the one found nearest to the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.31,0:24:01.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它形成于1亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt formed a hundred million years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.98,0:24:04.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它至少还有两倍的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and will be around at least twice that long...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.48,0:24:07.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,才会被银河系的旋臂撕碎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before the galaxy's spiral arms tear it apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.86,0:24:13.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,话说回来我们的太阳在孤独地运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Closer to home, our own Sun, orbiting in solitude...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.41,0:24:16.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许曾经就是疏散星团里恒星的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may have once been part of an open-cluster star...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.49,0:24:18.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,独自闯荡出来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that struck out on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.24,0:24:23.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳 星团 我们自己的地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun, the star clusters, our own planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.25,0:24:27.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上整个星系以至于宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in fact, the entire galaxy and the universe beyond...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.09,0:24:29.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都是尘埃和气体构成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are built of dust and gases.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.46,0:24:33.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在阻碍我们视线的这些粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These particles that now block ourview...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.47,0:24:36.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一开始就让我们来到了这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are what got us here in the first place...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.47,0:24:40.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星制造机器依然在不停地捣鼓\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the star-making machinery is still cranking.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.53,0:24:54.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,没有什么比得上辉煌的日落景观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nothing beats the spectacle of a glorious sunset...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.70,0:24:59.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而我们应将它归功于尘埃和气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we owe it all to dust and gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.33,0:25:05.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,夕阳表现出黄 橙甚至红色有两个原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The setting Sun appears yellow, orange, or even red for two reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.04,0:25:08.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,首先大气层里的大气分子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}First of all, the molecules of air in the atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.13,0:25:12.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将紫 蓝 绿光驱赶出了我们的视线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are scattering the violet, blue, and green light...out of our line of sight...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.71,0:25:16.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,留下黄 橙 红色进入我们眼帘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}leaving the yellows, oranges, and reds to reach our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.72,0:25:23.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,第二 大气层中尘埃或烟雾这样的微粒吸收蓝光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And second of all, particles like dust or smoke...or smog in the atmosphere absorb blue light...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.39,0:25:25.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,要多于它们吸收红光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}more than they do red light.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.69,0:25:32.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,甚至宏伟的蓝天其实是一种错觉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even the grandeur of a blue sky is really an optical illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.73,0:25:34.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天空为什么是蓝的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why is the sky blue?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.07,0:25:36.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的大气层中根本没有什么蓝色的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's nothing blue about the gases of our atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.78,0:25:39.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是由于阳光透过我们的大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but as sunlight comes through our atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.78,0:25:42.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,较短波长的蓝光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the shorterwavelengths, the blue light...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.16,0:25:44.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其散射要甚于较长的波长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}get scattered more than the longerwavelengths do.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.96,0:25:46.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以你注视天空任何特定的部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if you look at any particular part of the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.92,0:25:48.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你极有可能看到蓝光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you're more likely to see blue light...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.42,0:25:50.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被散射到你的眼中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}being scattered towards your eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.92,0:26:00.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太空一团漆黑是因为没有足够的气体或尘埃微粒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Space is dark because there aren't enough gas or dust particles...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.05,0:26:02.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来反射数十亿颗星光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to reflect the light of a billion stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.27,0:26:07.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,虽然太空可能是空无一物 但是并不完美\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And though space may be a vacuum, it's not perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.52,0:26:13.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,银河盘 银河系最大的部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The galactic disk, the largest portion of the Milky Way...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.53,0:26:17.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其质量的15%左右是尘埃和气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}owes about fifteen percent of its mass to dust and gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.20,0:26:23.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,气体云可以跨越数百甚至数千光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gas clouds can span hundreds or even thousands of light-years...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.83,0:26:27.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,为星系栩栩发光提供了原料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}providing the raw material that fires the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.62,0:26:31.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙尘埃和气体的区域称为星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These regions of cosmic dust and gas are called nebulae...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.96,0:26:35.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们产生的效果可以和地球上所见到的一切相媲美\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they produce effects rivaling anything seen on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.72,0:26:40.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个很好的例子就是猎户座星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A good example is the Orion Nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.97,0:26:43.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在猎户座里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the constellation Orion.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.31,0:26:46.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个区域活跃着恒星的形成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This region is active with stellarformation...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.43,0:26:49.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,使得恒星周围的气体光芒四射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which makes the gas around the stars glow.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.56,0:26:57.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它在星云旁的巨星发出的光线照射下荧光烁烁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's literally fluorescing in response to the light...coming out of the massive stars that are near the nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.24,0:27:00.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个星云通体被照亮 清晰可见\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this nebula literally glows and can be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.78,0:27:02.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你用肉眼就能看到它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can see it with your naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.08,0:27:05.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你看到猎户座星云时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you see the Orion Nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.66,0:27:09.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一定程度上 这些对我们来说是早期的图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a real way, those are baby pictures for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.04,0:27:12.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,50亿年前 我们就是在一个发光的热星云里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Five billion years ago, we were in a glowing hot nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.08,0:27:14.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳和行星一道形成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Sun and the planets were forming together...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.50,0:27:15.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,受到引力的影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}under the influence of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.09,0:27:20.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,猎户座 里面包含了高温星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Orion, which contains hot stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.43,0:27:23.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,紫外线电离它的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ionizing its gases with ultraviolet light...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.72,0:27:26.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被称为弥散或发射星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is called a diffuse or emission nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.27,0:27:32.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家分类了其他两类星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers classify two other categories of nebulae.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.81,0:27:35.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有些星云就是被称为发射星云的那一类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some nebulae are what are called reflection nebulae.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.86,0:27:38.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们很简单 这些星云里的尘埃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're simply... the dust in these nebulae...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.28,0:27:41.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只是反射附近的亮星的星光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is simply reflecting the starlight from the bright star nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.28,0:27:48.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,女巫头星云是反射星云的一个例子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Witch Head Nebula is an example of a reflection nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.87,0:27:51.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,借助于参宿七的星光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}borrowing light from the star Rigel.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.21,0:27:57.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,反射星云表现出蓝光的原因一如我们的天空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Reflection nebulae appear blue for the same reason our sky does.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.17,0:27:59.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,蓝光的反射比红光更加容易\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Blue light is more easily reflected than red.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.05,0:28:04.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最后是马头星云这样的暗星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And last there are dark nebulae like the Horsehead.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.77,0:28:11.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦像我们太阳这样的低质量的恒星死亡后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When low-mass stars like our Sun die...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.69,0:28:16.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们就会形成另一类星云叫做行星状星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they form another kind of nebula called a planetary nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.57,0:28:22.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些昏暗的寿命短暂的星云像猫眼星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These dim, short-lived nebulae, like the Cat's Eye Nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.53,0:28:25.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会将元素喷射回星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spew elements back into the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.78,0:28:30.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些会成为新太阳和新行星的原料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These may become raw materials for new suns and new planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.25,0:28:39.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像垂死的恒星喷出尘埃和气体云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just as dying stars spew out clouds of dust and gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.76,0:28:44.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尘埃和气体会结合在一起形成恒星一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dust and gas can come together to form stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.26,0:28:51.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在建筑工地上你看到旧建筑被推倒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At a construction site, you have old buildings being torn down...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.68,0:28:53.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,新建筑在建起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and new buildings going up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.60,0:28:57.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这几乎和银河系一模一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's very much the same in the Milky Way galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.19,0:28:59.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你看到老恒星爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You have old stars explode...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.32,0:29:02.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们抛出新材料 原材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they cast out new material, raw material...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.07,0:29:05.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,气体和尘埃可以用来形成新的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gas and dust that can be used to form new stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.03,0:29:12.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星云是星系的回收中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nebulae are the galaxy's recycling centers...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.79,0:29:15.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在这里变废为宝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where old becomes new again.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.29,0:29:18.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,回收利用不只是地球上的好主意\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Recycling is not just a good idea here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.79,0:29:22.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它是宇宙的自然法则\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a natural cosmic law.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.71,0:29:26.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上 我们的人体都是用回收的材料造就的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln fact, our own bodies are made out of recycled material...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.13,0:29:28.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来自早几代的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from earlier generations of stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.26,0:29:31.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,材料被分解成为星际介质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that had dispersed material into the interstellar medium...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.06,0:29:33.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是我们太阳系形成之前的事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before our own solar system formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.77,0:29:38.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,各代恒星都创造出了重元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each generation of stars creates heavier elements...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.56,0:29:41.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,成为宇宙万物的组成部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which become the ingredients for everything in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.65,0:29:45.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星系大部分高温 年轻的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the galaxy's hot, young stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.20,0:29:47.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是在银河系的旋臂里形成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}get built in the Milky Way's spiral arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.91,0:29:53.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,由于气体云如恒星那样围绕着星系中心运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As gas clouds orbit the center of the galaxy like the stars do...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.33,0:29:57.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在穿越旋臂时遭到了挤压\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they get squeezed as they go through a spiral arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.42,0:30:03.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,请记住旋臂仅仅是群星表现出的波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Remember, a spiral arm is simply a wave in the pattern of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.55,0:30:05.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为群星积聚在那里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And because stars are denser there...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.01,0:30:09.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,经过其中的气体云往往会被挤压\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gas clouds that orbit through it tend to get compressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.51,0:30:14.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那种挤压产生引力让气体抱团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That compression allows gravity to get a hold of that gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.22,0:30:16.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,导致它坍缩形成恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and cause it to collapse to form stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.48,0:30:18.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,要比其他地方更加容易\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}more readily there than anywhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.15,0:30:23.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星通常消亡在旋臂里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars often die in the spiral arms...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.69,0:30:26.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为它们在这里形成更加频繁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because they are formed here more frequently...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.19,0:30:29.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们中的牺牲者拥有巨大的质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}victims of their own enormous mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.20,0:30:32.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,较大质量的恒星非常强大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The more massive stars are extremely powerful...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.91,0:30:34.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,非常明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}extremely luminous.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.33,0:30:35.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,为了达到那样的亮度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And to be that luminous...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.54,0:30:40.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们不得不很快地消耗自己的能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they have to use up their energy source very quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.04,0:30:43.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此大质量恒星的寿命很短\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So massive stars live only short lives...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.80,0:30:50.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们于是就定居或靠近自己的出生地 旋臂里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they are thus found in or near their birthplaces, the spiral arms...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.30,0:30:52.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为它们根本没有足够的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because they simply don't have enough time...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.72,0:30:55.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,离开自己出生的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to wander away from the places where they were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.56,0:31:01.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管我们可以预期一些恒星的未来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although we can anticipate the future of some stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.56,0:31:04.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是往往很难了解它们的历史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's often difficult to learn their history.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.98,0:31:07.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而新科技正在揭示已经充分研究的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But new techniques are revealing new secrets...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.28,0:31:11.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,银河系里一颗叫做Mira A的恒星的秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about a well-studied star in the Milky Way called Mira A.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.57,0:31:16.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Mira 实际上是天文学家400年来一直很感兴趣的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mira has actually been a favorite star of astronomers for 400 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.08,0:31:18.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它是夜空中很容易看到的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a very easily visible star in the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.54,0:31:24.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最近星系演化探测器(GALEX)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Recently, the GALEX spacecraft, the Galaxy Evolution Explorer...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.21,0:31:28.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以看不见的紫外线拍摄了Mira\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}photographed Mira in invisible ultraviolet light...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.38,0:31:34.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,揭示出它在背后留下了13光年的足迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and revealed that it's leaving a trail thirteen light-years long behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.30,0:31:35.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们认为那实际上的原因是基于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We think that's actually caused by the fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.89,0:31:38.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,由于它穿过气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that as the star plows through the gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.68,0:31:40.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,气体随之加热激起震荡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gas heats up in a bow shock...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.94,0:31:43.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,非常像船只激起波澜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}very much like waves breaking up against a boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.86,0:31:47.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,于是那气流随着热物质流出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then that streams out into a wake of hot material.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.61,0:31:49.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你其实看到了Mira的活动 很大程度像条船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You're actually looking at Mira acting very much like a boat...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.99,0:31:51.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,劈波斩浪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}plowing through the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.82,0:31:53.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦你看到Mira现在有多快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you look at howfast Mira's going right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.87,0:31:56.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大约29.1万英里/小时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 291,000 miles an hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.28,0:31:57.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你就可以计算出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you do the calculations...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.74,0:32:01.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它那长长的尾巴是它最后的3万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that long tail is its path the last 30,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.37,0:32:04.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们无法准确预测太阳在其围绕着银河\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can't predict exactly where the Sun will go...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.04,0:32:05.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,运行的轨道上的具体位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in its orbit around the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.54,0:32:07.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有各种因素会对其产生影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's all kinds of things it could interact with.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.96,0:32:09.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是我们掌握了我们太阳的历史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But here we have the history of one star.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.63,0:32:11.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们知道这是它走的路\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know this is the path it took.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.97,0:32:14.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那将帮助我们模拟星系运作的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that'll help us model how the galaxyworks...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.64,0:32:17.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以及所有的恒星是如何围绕着星系中心运行的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and how all the stars move around the middle of the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.47,0:32:22.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在银河的郊区旋臂里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Within the Milky Way's suburban spiral arms...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.89,0:32:26.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,年轻的恒星拥有足够的活动空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}young stars enjoy plenty of space to move around.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.98,0:32:29.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦我们来到星系的凸出部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As we move into the galactic bulge...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.32,0:32:32.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,状况就变得拥挤不堪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}conditions get much more crowded and urban.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.49,0:32:34.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最靠近太阳的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The closest star to the Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.99,0:32:37.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,位于四光年多的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a little more than four light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.37,0:32:39.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当我们注视夜空时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when we look up into the night sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.37,0:32:42.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使是在周围没有亮光的十分晴朗的夜晚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even on a perfectly clear night with no lights around...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.75,0:32:46.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你所看到的星星不可能超过2000或者3000颗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you can't see more than about 2,000 or 3,000 stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.09,0:32:52.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 一旦我们的地球身处银河中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if our planet was down in the middle of the galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.67,0:32:56.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么夜空中就会有百万颗星星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there would be a million stars in the night sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.09,0:32:59.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最亮的恒星的亮度是我们在空中从未见过的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as bright as the brightest star that we've ever seen in our sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.68,0:33:02.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它将非常的亮 事实上没有夜晚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it would be so bright that, in fact, it wouldn't be nighttime.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.27,0:33:04.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将始终是白昼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt would be daytime all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.85,0:33:09.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不用多说 生活将完全不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Life, as we know it, would be completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.27,0:33:11.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么我们要把我们的位置放在什么地方呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So what do we owe our position to?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.61,0:33:16.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家认为引力做了大量的工作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists believe that gravity has a lot to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.95,0:33:25.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力是驱动星系的动力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity is the power that drives the galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.25,0:33:29.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在星系的中心 搅动着它提供动力的引擎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and at the galaxy's center, churns the engine it feeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.38,0:33:35.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星系就像座城市 里面始终在不断变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Galaxies are like a city in that they are ever-changing...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.05,0:33:38.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不断地重建和复兴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you're constantly being rebuilt and reinvigorated.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.18,0:33:42.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,毫无疑问银河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's no question that the Milky Way...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.52,0:33:43.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,几十亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a few billion years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.60,0:33:45.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其模样与今天的模样有很大的不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}looked a lot different than it does today.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.98,0:33:49.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它可能更小些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt probably was smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.06,0:33:52.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能不具备我们今天所见的美丽的螺旋状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt probably didn't have the beautiful spiral shape...that we see today.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.48,0:33:57.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着物体在引力作用下塌落 自然而然就形成了圆盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As things collapse under gravity, you tend to naturally form a disk.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.53,0:33:59.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你会注意到圆盘无处不在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You'll notice there are disks everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.41,0:34:02.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的太阳系是圆盘 我们的星系是圆盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our solar system is a disk, our galaxy is a disk.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.62,0:34:05.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 所有的恒星都向同一个方向运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the stars all start rotating in the same direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.75,0:34:13.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像一座城市星系里并非所有的恒星都是本地人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just as in a city, not all of the stars in the galaxy are natives.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.67,0:34:16.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有些恒星出生在银河系之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some stars, born beyond the Milky Way...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.47,0:34:19.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,落户在这 并且开始暂露头角\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}settle here and begin to make their mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.47,0:34:22.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而另一方面 如果有另一个星系经过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But then, if another galaxy comes by...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.85,0:34:25.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力会影响到恒星移动的路径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gravity affects the way the stars move...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.43,0:34:27.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它就可能加入到旋臂里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this may initiate the spiral arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.69,0:34:32.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此 事实上我们的螺旋状可能就是某种证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, in fact, our spiral shape may be some evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.65,0:34:35.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,说明银河系是由多个小星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the Milky Way is composed of more than one small galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.44,0:34:37.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在很久以前走在一起构成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that came together a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.95,0:34:42.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在历史上星系的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Historically, the center of the galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.16,0:34:44.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一直存在着一个难以看透的秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been an impenetrable mystery...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.99,0:34:48.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,直到我们开发出X射线观察\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until we developed X-ray vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.29,0:34:51.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们真正识别出银河系中心的准确位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the first ways we really identified...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.17,0:34:53.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,的一个最早的手段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the exact center of the galaxywas...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.17,0:34:55.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是利用X射线望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was with an X-ray telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.09,0:34:57.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,X射线能够穿透\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, the X-rays were able to pass through...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.30,0:35:00.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们星系盘里所有的尘埃和气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all of the dust and gas in the disk of our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.30,0:35:04.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此 尽管我们无法真正看到星系明亮的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so, even though we can't really see this bright center to the galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.31,0:35:07.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是在X射线里 这个巨大的 熊熊燃烧的热源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in X-rays, there's this giant, glowing hot source...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.48,0:35:09.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就在中央\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}right in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.14,0:35:12.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,X射线发射体 人马座A星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The X-ray emitter, Sagittarius A star...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.27,0:35:17.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,联系着银河系中心的超大质量的黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is associated with the supermassive black hole...in the Milky Way's center.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.49,0:35:23.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,按照定义黑洞不允许光甚至X射线逃逸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By definition, a black hole doesn't allow light...or even X-rays to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.83,0:35:27.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,气体的辐射射物被黑洞引力困住\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The radiation comes from gas caught in its gravity...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.37,0:35:31.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,旋转并加热到数百万度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spun and heated to millions of degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.46,0:35:35.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们的移动速度极高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're moving at extremely high velocities.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.96,0:35:40.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比如我们已经能够观察到的更为极端的案例\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For example, the more extreme cases that we've been able to observe...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.09,0:35:43.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星在经过黑洞时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the stars are moving as they pass by the black hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.97,0:35:47.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其速度达到了一万公里/秒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at a speed of10,000 kilometers per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.93,0:35:51.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那就像在四秒钟里绕地球一圈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's like going around the world in four seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.23,0:35:56.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们谈到了整个恒星以那样的速度移动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we're talking about a whole star moving at that speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.19,0:36:01.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们看到了恒星围绕着我们银河系的最中心运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we watch stars orbiting the very center of our galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.40,0:36:04.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,显然那里有某种看不见的怪物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's obvious that there's some sort of invisible monster there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.20,0:36:08.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们都围绕着一个巨大的质量运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're orbiting around a giant mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.41,0:36:10.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星的运转暗示着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the orbits of the stars imply that there's about...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.71,0:36:13.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大约是太阳3到4百万倍的质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}three to four million times the mass of the Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.75,0:36:15.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,存在于我们星系的最中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the very center of our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.88,0:36:19.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们不清楚谁先出现 是星系呢 还是黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're not sure which came first, the galaxy or the black hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.21,0:36:22.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是我们知道它是存在的 是个庞然大物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we know that it's there, and it's tremendous.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.39,0:36:28.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,虽然它强大又怪异 但这个超大质量黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For all its power and weirdness, the supermassive black hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.31,0:36:32.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对银河系这样大小的星系是相当典型的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is pretty typical for a galaxy the size of the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.77,0:36:36.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其它螺旋形系和大椭圆星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Other spiral galaxies and big elliptical galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.02,0:36:40.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们的中心似乎也有超大质量黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}also seem to have supermassive black holes in their middle...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.03,0:36:44.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,范围从我们太阳质量的100万倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ranging from a million times the mass of our Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.07,0:36:47.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一直到我们太阳质量的几十亿倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}up to several billion times the mass of our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.74,0:36:53.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,围绕黑洞的恒星都上年岁了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars surrounding the black hole are ancient.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.08,0:36:57.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,许多是比我们太阳大数百倍的红巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many are red giants, hundreds oftimes bigger than our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.38,0:37:01.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,银河的中心挤满了它们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The galactic center is crowded with them...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.09,0:37:04.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像市中心里人满为患\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like an urban downtown crowded with people.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.26,0:37:08.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星和人一样爱出风头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And stars, like people, can be pushy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.43,0:37:10.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,银河系中心的多数恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most stars in the galactic center...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.85,0:37:13.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只是围绕着中心黑洞不停地运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}simplyjust keep orbiting the central black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.73,0:37:14.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而在银河中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in the galactic center...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.89,0:37:16.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有太多的恒星相互挤得很近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there are so many stars packed so close together...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.02,0:37:19.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以至于恒星始终在相互推搡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that stars are constantly nudging each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.44,0:37:20.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一点点引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a little bit gravitationally.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.86,0:37:23.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们的轨道一直遭到干扰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And their orbits are being perturbed...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.69,0:37:24.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,少许遭到改变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}changed a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.66,0:37:29.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,遭受碰撞的恒星会被剥夺走大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A bumped star can get stripped of its atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.78,0:37:32.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只留下其运转的核心部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}leaving just its orbiting core.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.25,0:37:36.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或者难得会滚进黑洞然后消失得无影无踪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or, rarely, it can tumble into the black hole and vanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.75,0:37:41.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而还有事情正发生在黑洞的周围\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But something else is happening around the black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.63,0:37:44.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个动荡不安的地区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This turbulent, dangerous neighborhood...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.80,0:37:47.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也是个恒星育婴所\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is also a stellar nursery.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.64,0:37:52.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们观察到的正飞快地围绕着黑洞运转的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars that we're observing...moving fastest around the black hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.52,0:37:56.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都是最近才形成的年轻恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are the young stars that have very recently formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.89,0:37:59.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那个情况被我们称之为青春悖论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's something we call the paradox of youth...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.73,0:38:01.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为很难想象是如何在黑洞面前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it's hard to imagine how to form...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.98,0:38:05.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,形成这些大量的年轻恒星的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}these massive young stars in the presence of a black hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.28,0:38:06.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可是它们就在那里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and yet there they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.82,0:38:10.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,近来科学家发现了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Recently, astronomers discovered...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.83,0:38:13.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,并非所有的恒星都受黑洞的掌控\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that not all stars caught in the black hole's grip...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.00,0:38:15.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,注定要呆在那里的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are doomed to stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.00,0:38:21.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有些会设法逃脱去拜访宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A few manage to break away and see the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.63,0:38:25.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,高速行走在宇宙间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Barreling through the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.01,0:38:29.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,时速达150万英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at one and a half million miles per hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.47,0:38:33.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,超高速恒星是星系的逃亡者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hyper-velocity stars are the escapees of the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.85,0:38:37.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,高速恒星的有趣之处在于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what's interesting about high-velocity stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.23,0:38:39.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,解释它们极端的速度的唯一方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the only way to explain their extreme velocities...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.69,0:38:42.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是它们是被超大质量的黑洞弹射出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that they were ejected by a supermassive black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.15,0:38:45.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星要被弹射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For a star to go ballistic...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.69,0:38:49.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,要采取一套非常特殊的环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}takes a very specific set of circumstances...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.53,0:38:52.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上它需要两个恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, in fact, it requires two stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.49,0:38:55.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你抬头看到的大多数恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the stars you see in the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.49,0:39:00.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,并不是单个的恒星 而是成双成对的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are not single stars, but pairs or binary stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.04,0:39:07.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们相互围绕运转 依靠引力联系在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They orbit around each other, linked by gravity's embrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.88,0:39:10.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而银河中心的恒星对子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But a star pair in the galactic center...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.34,0:39:13.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能会遭到周围恒星的推挤\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}might getjostled by surrounding stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.05,0:39:15.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在黑洞很近的地方游荡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and stray too close to the black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.10,0:39:18.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦发生这种情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When that happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.39,0:39:21.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,此刻黑洞的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the moment that the gravitational pull of the black hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.73,0:39:25.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就会超过把两颗恒星约束在一起的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exceeds the gravity that's binding the two stars together...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.36,0:39:28.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这对恒星就会被扯开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the pair of stars is broken apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.19,0:39:30.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其中的一颗恒星就会被黑洞抓住\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the stars will be captured by the black hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.99,0:39:33.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通常会进入围绕黑洞的非常贴近的轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}usually into a very tight orbit around the black hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.62,0:39:34.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而另一颗恒星则会获得\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the other star will then gain...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.74,0:39:37.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其系统的全部能量 会以难以置信的速度弹出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the energy of that system and it'll be ejected...with this incredible velocity.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.04,0:39:41.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果星系是个城市的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf the galaxy were a city...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.29,0:39:44.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么大多数的恒星就是汽车或行人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where most of the stars would be cars or pedestrians...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.92,0:39:51.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,高速恒星就更像是冲出城市的飞机或高速列车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a high-velocity star would be more like an airplane...or a high-speed train rushing out of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.59,0:39:57.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你呆在一个高速恒星上驾乘是相当惊人的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf you were on a high-velocity star, the ride would be quite amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.47,0:39:59.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天上布满了恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The sky would be covered with stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.43,0:40:01.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,四面八方如满月般的亮星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as bright as the full Moon in every direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.77,0:40:03.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是那种景观很快就会改变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But that view would quickly change...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.44,0:40:06.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为高速恒星很快就飞出了星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}'cause the high-velocity star moves so quickly out of the galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.11,0:40:08.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星星在夜空中会越来越稀少\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the stars would appear fewer and fewer in the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.49,0:40:13.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,银河系在不断地运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The galaxy is constantly in motion...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.20,0:40:16.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像是一个巨大的轮子或不断延伸的大都会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like a giant wheel or a sprawling metropolis.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.58,0:40:19.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在城市的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln the heart of town...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.95,0:40:23.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,超大质量黑洞的引力搅动着周围的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the supermassive black hole's gravity whips stars around...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.12,0:40:25.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,约11分钟转动一圈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in an orbit of around eleven minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.63,0:40:31.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球坐落的位置 是在一条旋臂三分之二的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Where the Earth sits, two-thirds of the way out on a spiral arm...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.72,0:40:36.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们穿越银河系 每次需要2.5亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we traverse the Milky Way once every 250 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.39,0:40:40.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的太阳系走完街区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our solar system has been around the block...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.56,0:40:43.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,自形成以来只有18次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}only eighteen times since it formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.56,0:40:47.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,银河系难以估摸的尺度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Milky Way's incomprehensible size...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.57,0:40:51.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,使它很容易忘记自己只是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}makes it easy to forget it's just one small part...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.28,0:40:53.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不断膨胀的宇宙的很小一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of an expanding universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.16,0:40:55.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,人们听说膨胀的宇宙时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When people hear about the expanding universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.95,0:40:58.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,普遍的误解就是一切都在膨胀之中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a common misconception is that everything is expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.83,0:41:01.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上我现在就没有膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in fact, l'm not expanding right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.45,0:41:03.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我的原子大小没变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}My atoms are the same size.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.16,0:41:04.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我的细胞大小没变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}My cells are the same size.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.67,0:41:08.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球也没有渐渐远离太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth is not getting farther away from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.88,0:41:12.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙的膨胀只适用于天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The expansion of the universe only applies to celestial objects...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.34,0:41:14.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,并未因为引力而结合在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that aren't bound together by gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.68,0:41:17.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为银河系里的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since the planets within the Milky Way...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.76,0:41:19.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,受到的引力拉扯要强于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have stronger gravitational pulls...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.72,0:41:23.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们外部星系的张力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than the expanding forces outside our galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.14,0:41:27.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以宇宙的膨胀并未影响到我们太阳系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the expansion of the universe doesn't affect our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.90,0:41:31.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们自己的银河系 一个螺旋形系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our own Milky Way, a spiral galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.57,0:41:34.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,已经遭到了另一个螺旋形系的碰撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is on a collision course with another spiral galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.90,0:41:36.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们附近最大的螺旋星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the largest spiral near us...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.41,0:41:38.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它就是仙女座星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that is the Andromeda galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.32,0:41:42.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们认为或许在3 40亿年间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We think that in maybe three orfour billion years...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.16,0:41:44.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们两个星系会结合在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our two galaxies may merge together.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.87,0:41:46.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看到那样的情景是非常有趣的事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt will be very interesting to see what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.25,0:41:51.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许不会发生恒星的碰撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What probably won't happen is a collision of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.30,0:41:55.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管两个星系包含了数十亿颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even though both galaxies contain billions of stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.93,0:41:57.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是它们之间的距离是非常大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the space between them is enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.05,0:42:02.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们会有引力的相互作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They will gravitationally interact...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.26,0:42:05.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,改变它们的方向和运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}changing their direction and motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.06,0:42:08.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最终 联姻的螺旋星系将尘埃落定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eventually, the merged spirals will settle down...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.52,0:42:10.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,成为一个椭圆星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to become an elliptical galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.90,0:42:16.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从本质上讲 我们本星系里所有几十个星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Essentially, all of the several dozen galaxies in our local group...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.11,0:42:19.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都会成为一个超星系的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will be part of one supergalaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.24,0:42:23.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,于是慢慢地超星系会开始丧失恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then, gradually, that supergalaxy will start losing stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.87,0:42:28.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,原因就在于那个星系里的恒星之间的引力作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because of gravitational interactions among the stars within that galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.50,0:42:32.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有些会飞进星系之间的太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some will get flung away into intergalactic space.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.84,0:42:39.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在它最初形成时银河系快速形成群星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it first formed, the Milky Way built stars at a rapid pace...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.55,0:42:44.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,利用大爆炸喷射进太空里的原材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}using raw materials that were ejected in space from the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.06,0:42:45.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着星系年龄的增大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the galaxy aged...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.77,0:42:49.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星的生产从每年几百个慢慢降到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the star production slowed down from a few hundred a year...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.35,0:42:53.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如今每年4到6个新恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to about four to six new stars each year today.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.40,0:42:56.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着时间的推移银河系变化天翻地覆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over time, the Milky Way galaxy has changed dramatically...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.19,0:42:58.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们不能确切地知道它很久以前的样子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we don't know exactly what it looked like long ago.
